<s> Yes they can - in fact the original legitimate use of -- -- was in DTD to comment out examples of the constructs being defined.  </s>
<s> However it is not particularly safe, as some browsers parse SGML comments incorrectly.  </s>
<s> Also the comments are unsafe because they use strings of hyphens.  </s>
<s> Each -- toggles comment status on and off, so you have to be very careful to get the right number (also an area where many browsers don't obey the rules).  </s>
<s> And the screen shots should have been GIF or PNG; this is a case where JPEG produces larger files and the JPEG artefacts can be a real problem.  </s>
<s> NB HTML is not a page description language; you shouldn't be surprised if some browsers even speak your page and shouldn't expect exactly the same format; use PDF if you want precise formatting.  </s>
